				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I completely agree with Twile and all the stuff that he's saying because it basically follows a lot of logical sense when you think about it. I mean, smaller ships have the manuverability advantage that a much larger ship just wouldn't have the same speed and ability to move out of the way. I've never really played a lot of space battle games but of course I have watched Star Wars and they take down those big ships all the time with a ton of small ones. Sure they're easy to kill with one well placed laser blast but when its perhaps about 20 doomies against oh say 2000 gunboats I'd probably put my bets in with the boats. Though in this sort of thing you would think for a fleet perhaps you could have a multitude of ships, like somehow the Doomies can hold gunboats that they can send out when the fights are drawing closer together and then have those, of course under another commie, attack at the opposing force without having to worry about getting close enough while going under the heavy fire that doomies can fire out at them. Because, if you think about it once they get in close enough it really should be near impossible for the doomies to actually fire at and hit them without hitting their own allies and possibly helping out the fleets of gunboats in the process of doing that. There really is a bunch of factors in this that I'm missing and who knows, I could be completely wrong about my own assumptions but I'm admitably not that bright. And I remember back when I was first starting and building a doomie for me too over a 100 turns. What could I do when I was attacked by fleets of multiple doomies when all I had at the most was a few Dreadnaughts and maybe a Mobile Fortress or two? Stuff like that nearly turned me off the game and probably did for a lot of people. If it was possible for the newer players to be able to atleast stand a slight chance against attacking doomstars maybe we'd have more people wanting to play AS.
<br />
All in all, I agree with Twile basically and just wanted to throw in my two cents in the whole matter. You can argue and stuff with me if you like and point out flaws in what I said cause there are probably tons of 'em.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
